name: Skagit County Public Health- Fairgrounds
notes:
Pfizer Dose 1 & 2 Vaccine Clinic 
•	North Entrance to Skagit County Fairgrounds 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Child watching provided
•	Vaccination process will take approximately 1 hour.  Wheel chairs and accessible parking available for people with mobility challenges.
•	All forms available in English and Spanish.  Spanish language interpretation provided.  
•	Dose 2 appointments scheduled 3 weeks following 

We are unable to vaccinate people who have received another vaccine of any type within 14 days OR those that have severe allergic reactions to vaccines or injectable medications.


Clínica de vacunas de primer y Segundo dosis Pfizer
•	Entrada norte al recinto ferial del condado de Skagit 1410 Virginia Street, Mount Vernon WA
•	Vigilancia de niños proveída
•	El proceso de vacunación durará aproximadamente 1 hora. Sillas de ruedas y estacionamiento accesible para personas con problemas de movilidad.
•	Todos los formularios están disponibles en inglés y español. Interpretación en español será proveída.

No podemos vacunar a personas que hayan recibido otra vacuna de cualquier tipo durante los ultimos 14 días O personas que tengan reacciones alérgicas graves a vacunas o medicamentos inyectables.
Citas reservadas 3 semanas después para la segunda dosis.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Ocean Shores Convention Center

address.street1: 120 West Chance a La Mer Northwest

notes: This clinic is held within the Ocean Shores Convention Center. This clinic is for the 2nd dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine and the one-dose Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) COVID-19 vaccine. Both the Moderna vaccine and the Janssen vaccine is only available to adults 18 years and older. The supply of the Janssen vaccine is limited. For the 2nd Moderna dose, you must have had the MODERNA VACCINE for your first vaccine in order to get the second dose of the Moderna vaccine. You CANNOT mix brands of the COVID-19 vaccine. Please bring a face covering to your appointment that covers the mouth and the nose and, if you are getting your second dose, please bring your vaccination card. If you cannot locate your vaccine card, proof of first vaccination and type of vaccine must be provided. All persons receiving the vaccine are required to stay under observation 15-30 minutes post-vaccination.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes: ***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Upload options 1. Prepmod at time of sign up 2. bring your insurance card to your visit. We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine. Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine. Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available. Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
